1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 c5 4. Bb5+ Nc6
{ This avoids simplifications. If White exchanges on  c6  , Black gets the bishop pair and a strong center after bxc6. }
5. Nf3 cxd4 6. Qxd4 Ne7 7. O-O Bd7 8. Bxc6 bxc6 9. c4 c5
{ After the queen retreats, Black can play d4 followed by Bc6 giving Black full control of the diagonal  a8  -  h1  . This together with the bishop pair give Black the better position. }
