1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 c5 4. Bb5+ Nc6
{ This avoids simplifications. If White exchanges on  c6  , Black gets the bishop pair and a strong center after bxc6. }
5. Nf3 cxd4 6. Nxd4 Bd7 7. Nxc6 Bxc6 8. Bxc6+ bxc6 9. O-O Ne7 10. Qe2 Ng6
{ Ng6 should be followed by Be7 or Bc5 and O-O.   Note   If there is a black knight on  g6  and a black bishop on  e7  , White can often play h4 and h5. After h5, the knight has to retreat to  f8  or  h8  depending on whether or not Black has already castled. This is not necessarily bad for Black, but it should be checked. }
*

