1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 c5 4. Qg4 Nc6 5. Nf3 Qa5+ 6. Nc3 a6
{ This move is necessary to prepare a safe retreat to  c7  for the queen after Bd2. }
7. Bd2 Qc7 8. Bd3 cxd4 9. Ne2 Nxe5 10. Nxe5 Qxe5 11. Bf4 Nf6 12. Qg3 Qh5
{ Black is currently two pawns up, and if White takes on  d4  to regain one of them, then Black can play Qg4 to exchanges queens. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "2. Various 4th Moves"]
[Black "4. Qg4 6. Nc3 2*"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 c5 4. Qg4 Nc6 5. Nf3 Qa5+ 6. Nc3 a6
{ to prepare a safe retreat on  c7  for the queen after Bd2   6...Bd7  7.Bd2 }
7. Bd2 Qc7 8. O-O-O h5 9. Qf4
{ There are three reasons for inserting h5 9. Qf4:   - to reduce the pressure on  g7   - to win a tempo with Ng6 after Nge7   - to stop White from stabilizing the center with  f4  after cxd4 10. Nxd4  (the queen is in the way)  . }
9... cxd4 10. Nxd4 Nge7 11. Nxc6 bxc6
{ The pawn on  e5  is weak, and Black gets control of the center with c5 and/or Ng6. }
*

