{ This is Berg's suggestion. } 8. Bxh6
{ This move does not work since Qxb2 attacks both the rook on  a1  and the knight on  c3  . }
8... Qxb2 9. Rd1 Qxc3+ 10. Bd2 Qxc2 11. dxc5 Qg6
{ The manoeuver Qc2-g6, or Qc2-h7 if h7-h6 has been played, is quite typical for the French. Transferring the queen, or in some cases the bishop, to the kingside via this route is an effective way to defend against a queen on  g4  . }
12. Qxg6 hxg6 13. Rc1 f6 *

