1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 c5 4. c3 Nc6 5. g3 Qa5
{ Watson's suggestion. Black threatens cxd4. } 6. dxc5 Qc7 7. f4 Bxc5 8. Nf3
Nge7
{ White is behind in development and cannot castle at the moment.   I prefer Nge7 to Nh6 because I find the extra option Ng6 more useful than Ng4 and because the square  e7  is not needed by the bishop.  Black will open the center with a quick f6. If White takes on  f6  then gxf6, Ng6, O-O and e5 give Black plenty of play. If White lets Black take on e5 then Ng6, O-O and Rxf3 are an option. }
*

