12. Nxc6 Qxc6 13. Qe2 O-O 14. Re1 Bd6
{ This is the idea. If White takes on e6 now then the rook is misplaced on e1. }
15. Qxe6+
{ 15.Nd2  e5  16.dxe5  Bxe5  and White cannot take on e5.  17.Qxe5?  Rae8 }
15... Kh8
{ Black threatens Bxh2 and Rae8 is a much stronger threat now with the white rook on e1. Also the square f2 is now without the protection of the rook. Black has full compensation for the pawn. }
