Nh6
{ Playing Nh6 is a bit doubled edged. Usually when Black castles long and White short, or if this is at least likely to happen, then the half-open files, the bishop pair and the potential weakness of the pawn on  e5  are compensation enough for the doubled pawn.   Here there is one additional feature. The Black queen has not moved to  c7  yet so if White takes on  h6  Black also has the move Qe7 which defends  h7  and can create extra pressure on the half-open g-file with Qg7 and Rg8. }
9. Bxh6 gxh6 10. Nbd2 Qe7 11. O-O O-O-O
{ Black can start putting pressure on  e5  and the king with Qg7 next. } *

