{ Indirectly protecting  e5  with the discovered check on  h5  . } 9... O-O-O
10. c4 d4 11. Bd3 Nh6 { Be7 first is also good. } 12. Bg5 Re8 13. Nbd2 Nf7 14.
Bf4 Be7 15. Ne4 Ref8 16. Qd2 g5
{ This is not a pawn sacrifice but just an exchange. Black gets the pawn on  e5  in return for  g5  . }
17. Nexg5 Nxg5 18. Nxg5 Bxg5 19. Bxg5 Nxe5 20. Bh4
{ The best move. White wants to pin the knight with Bg3. On  g3  the bishop will also block any future attack on the g-file. }
20... Nxd3 21. Qxd3 e5 22. Bg3 Re8 23. Re2 Re7 24. Rae1 Rhe8 25. Bh4 Rf7
{ I think the position is equal. It may look as if White has a bit of pressure, but even if the pawn on  e5  should be lost, I don't see how White can win. The opposite-colored bishops and the protected passed pawn on  d4  should be enough for a comfortable draw. }
