{ The best move. } 7... fxe5 { This clarifies the situation in the center. } 8.
Nxe5 Nxe5 9. dxe5 Qc7 10. f4
{ As soon as you see f4 in the Advance French, you should start considering Nh6. Here it turns out to be a good move as well. Without f4, Nh6 would be questionable before castling since White can take and then play Bh5. But now that option does not exist any longer.   That being said, there are three separate setups which are all interesting and good for Black:    (i)  O-O-O and Ne7,    (ii)  O-O-O and Nh6 and    (iii)  Nh6, Be7 and O-O.   If you want to play one of the first two setups then you should play O-O-O, if it is one of the latter two then you should start with Nh6 for maximal flexibility. }
10... O-O-O 11. Na3 Ne7 12. Nc2 { This was the point of Na3. } 12... g5
{ Since defending the f-pawn with g3 will likely lead to a quick win for Black  (g-file, Bc6)  , White has to take on  g5  . But then  e5  gets very weak. }
13. fxg5 Ng6 *

