Nxe5 Nxe5 9. dxe5 Qc7 10. Bf4 O-O-O
{ Black castles to prepare h6 and g5. After the immediate h6 White has Bh5+. }
11. b4 Ne7
{ 11...c4  now is not good. White can play  12.a4  followed by   Na3  (, Nb5 and Be3 forcing Black to move the a- or b-pawn. After that White's attack on the queenside will be much faster than anything Black can generate on the kingside.) }
12. Nd2 { 12.bxc5  Ng6  is fine for Black. } 12... c4
