Nxe5 Nxe5 9. dxe5 Qc7 10. c4 O-O-O 11. Re1
{ This is one of the main lines of the 6. Be2 f6 variation. It looks a bit dangerous but Black can take the pawn on e5. }
11... Qxe5 12. Nc3 Nf6 { Rapid development is the key in this variation. } 13.
g3 { Preparing Bf4 to harass the queen. } 13... Qf5
{ Probably the best square for the queen.  After Bd3 Black's queen can go to  g4  or  h3  . }
