Nxd4 9. Ng5 Nc6 10. Qe2 Nb4 11. Bxh7
{ What else? If White lets Black take the bishop, then there is not much of an attack. }
11... Nh6 12. Rd1
{ White covers  d4  so that after Be3, Black cannot respond with d4. } 12...
Be7 { Black simply threatens to take the knight and then the bishop. } 13. Be3
Qc7 14. a3 Nc6 15. Bd3 Nf5 16. Bxf5 Qxe5
{ A cute zwischenzug to keep the pawn structure intact. } 17. Nf3 Qxf5 *

