{ Still the best chance for White. The queen should go to  f3  to put pressure on  f7  . }
10... Bc5 { Aiming for  f2  . } 11. Qf3 Nh6
{ An important motive. The square  f7  is protected, and if White takes on  h7  , then the half-open h-file and the insecure position of the piece on  h7  give Black the advantage. }
12. Nc3 Nd4
{ The idea of this move is to follow up with Nhf5. The two knights in the center block most attempts to generate an attack. The attack with g4 has to be checked at every move, and unfortunately, there does not seem to be an easy way to remember all the tactical nuances. }
13. Qh3 Nhf5 14. g4 Ne7
{ White's attacking formation only makes sense if Black castles short. } *

