1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 c5 4. c3 Nc6 5. Nf3 Bd7 6. Bd3 cxd4 7. cxd4 Qb6 8. O-O
Nxd4 9. Nxd4 Qxd4 10. Nc3 a6 11. Re1
{ White wants to play Qf3 without allowing Qxe5. } 11... Ne7 12. Be3
{ Allows Qe5 after all, since after   12.Qf3  Ng6  White has difficulties with defending the e-pawn as well. }
12... Qxe5 13. Qf3 Bc6 14. Bf4 Qf6 15. Qg3 Ng6
{ This is the reason why it is better to take on  e5  only after Ne7 has been played. Otherwise, the Bf4, Qg3 battery on the dark squares is difficult to handle. }
16. Bg5 Bd6 { Black is better. } *

