Nxd4 9. Nxd4 Qxd4 10. Nc3 a6 11. Qe2 Qh4
{ This is just a suggestion for people trying to avoid the mainlines. Black plans Nh6 and Ng4 and perhaps Rc8, Bc5 and O-O. If the queen is needed on the queenside, it can always return via  d8  . The move is perfectly fine for Black. Nonetheless, I believe that 11. ... Ne7 is a little bit stronger. }
