[Black "New mainline (9. Nbd2)  10. Nxd4 2"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 c5 4. c3 Nc6 5. Nf3 Bd7 6. Bd3 cxd4 7. cxd4 Qb6 8. O-O
Nxd4 9. Nbd2 Bc5
{ The moves Ne7 and Nxf3 are also popular. It is not easy to decide which is best. I chose Bc5 because the idea behind it is straightforward. The bishop protects the knight on  d4  in order to prepare Bb5. Once the knight is protected by the bishop, the black queen is free to recapture on  b5  if necessary. }
10. Nxd4 Bxd4
{ Black continues with Ne7 and the Nc6 or Ng6. Black does not mind exchanging the knight on  d2  for the bishop on  d4  because without knights the weakness of the dark squares, especially  d6  , does not matter so much. }
11. Qe2 Ne7 12. Nb3 Nc6 13. Bf4 Nb4
{ The bishop cannot escape because of Bb5. } *

