10. b4 Nxf3+ 11. Nxf3 Qxb4
{ Taking with the bishop would be a mistake. White is much better after Rb1.   White's main choices after Qxb4 are Rb1 and Ng5. After other moves Black can simply play b6 and prevent white's rook from reaching  b7  . }
12. Rb1 Qa4
{ Black is willing to return one of the two extra pawns in order to exchange queens. This manoeuver is the key to this whole line. }
13. Qe2 b6 { Black keeps his extra pawns. } *

