12. Rb1 { 12.Qg3  Ne7  13.Rb1  Qa4  transposes to 12.Rb1 Qa413.Qg3 Ne7 } 12...
Qa4 13. Qg3
{ Here we see the reason for Qxf3. Black does not threaten to exchange queens on d1 so White can take the pawn on b7 while keeping the queens on the board.   13.Rxb7  Ne7  14.Qg3  O-O  transposes to 13.Qg3 Ne7 14. Rxb7 O-O }
13... Ne7 14. Nf3 Bc6 15. Qxg7 Rg8 16. Qf6
